Step 1 — Create the directory (if it doesn’t exist)
sudo mkdir -p /usr/news-t1q2/

Step 2 — Create the template YAML file

You can use nano or vi to create the file:

sudo nano /usr/news-t1q2/news-t1q2.yml

Step 3 — Add the Pod template content

Paste the following into the file:

apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: news-nginx-t1q2
  labels:
    app: news-nginx
spec:
  containers:
    - name: nginx-container
      image: nginx
  restartPolicy: Always


Explanation:

apiVersion: v1 → standard for Pod creation

kind: Pod → defines a Pod

metadata.name → name of the Pod (news-nginx-t1q2)

metadata.labels → allows selecting/filtering the pod easily later

containers → defines a single container using nginx image

restartPolicy: Always → default policy for Pods, ensures it restarts on failure

Step 4 — Save the file and exit

In nano → Ctrl+O (save), Ctrl+X (exit)

Step 5 — Test creating the Pod using the template
kubectl apply -f /usr/news-t1q2/news-t1q2.yml
kubectl get pods -l app=news-nginx
kubectl describe pod news-nginx-t1q2


You should see the Pod Running and using the nginx image.